<subSubSection id="C304FCE67611FFD769901EBB117BFD27" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA1AF6D7611FFD769901EBB117BFD27" blockId="30.[151,1437,152,642]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7611FFD769901EBB135FFE65" bold="true" box="[197,322,422,448]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Remarks:</emphasis>
Externally 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7611FFD7689A1EBA111FFE65" box="[463,770,423,448]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinorum">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7611FFD7689A1EBA111FFE65" box="[463,770,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Hemipenthes martinorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7611FFD76AF41EBA1600FE65" box="[929,1053,423,448]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wilcoxi">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7611FFD76AF41EBA1600FE65" box="[929,1053,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">H. wilcoxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the white scales on the fifth and seventh abdominal tergites and the smooth color margin in wing. The smooth color margin and the identical shape of the genitalia relate 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7611FFD76A0E1EE91613FDA8" box="[859,1038,500,525]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinorum">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7611FFD76A0E1EE91613FDA8" box="[859,1038,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">H. martinorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<emphasis id="B96A737F7611FFD76D011EE91759FDA8" box="[1108,1348,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7611FFD76D011EE916D6FDA8" box="[1108,1227,500,525]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="celeris">H. celeris</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7611FFD76D8D1EE91722FDA8" box="[1240,1343,500,525]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curta">H. curta</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7611FFD76C2A1EE91319FD96" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pleuralis">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7611FFD76C2A1EE91319FD96" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">H. pleuralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species has an uncommon distribution, as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7611FFD76A2A1D071618FD96" box="[895,1029,538,563]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incisiva">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7611FFD76A2A1D071618FD96" box="[895,1029,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">H. incisiva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it can not be said if this disjunct distribution is real or an effect of the rarity or difficulty to collect this species. Only two specimens from Michoacán, 
<collectingCountry id="F309EFFD7611FFD7687D1D75139CFD27" box="[296,385,616,642]" name="Mexico" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Mexico</collectingCountry>
were available in the revised collections.
</paragraph>
